<concept id="concept_epd_zwt_c2b">
    <title>Book Rooms</title>
    <shortdesc>You can book rooms for old guests and new guests.</shortdesc>
    <prolog>
        <author type="creator">Carol</author>
        <critdates>
            <created date="2018/06/11"/>
            <!--Carol-->
            <revised modified="2018/06/11"/>
        </critdates>
    </prolog>
    <conbody>
        <section id="section_u4f_bxt_c2b">
            <title>Book Rooms for New Guests</title>
            <p>If it is the first
                <?oxy_insert_start author="Becky" timestamp="20191127T131521+0800"?>time for
                <?oxy_insert_end?>the guest
                <?oxy_insert_start author="Becky" timestamp="20191127T131544+0800"?>to
                <?oxy_insert_end?>come to the hotel, you can book a room for the guest on the
                    <b>Booking List</b> page.</p>
            <p>
                <ol id="ol_pt1_fzt_c2b">
                    <li>Go to <menucascade>
                            <uicontrol>Hotel</uicontrol>
                            <uicontrol>Room Operations</uicontrol>
                            <uicontrol>Booking List</uicontrol>
                        </menucascade>, click <uicontrol>Add</uicontrol>.</li>
                    <li>Select a
                        room<?oxy_insert_start author="Becky" timestamp="20191127T131704+0800"?>
                        type<?oxy_insert_end?>, and set the check-in time and check-out time.</li>
                    <li>Enter the guest information. The <b>First Name</b> and <b>Last Name</b> are
                        required fields.</li>
                    <li>Check the option <b>Send Email</b> on the bottom of the edit page, the
                        system will send a booking notification to the guestâ€™s email address.</li>
                    <li>Click <uicontrol>Save</uicontrol>.</li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section id="section_mlb_kzt_c2b">
            <title>Book Rooms for Old Guests</title>
            <p>If the guest has stayed in the hotel before, the guest information will be kept in
                the hotel system. Next time, when the guest wants to book a room, you can operate
                the booking on <b>Guest List</b> page.</p>
            <p>
                <ol id="ol_mdt_lzt_c2b">
                    <li>Go to <menucascade>
                            <uicontrol>Hotel</uicontrol>
                            <?oxy_insert_start author="Becky" timestamp="20191127T131903+0800"?>
                            <uicontrol>Room Operations</uicontrol>
                            <?oxy_insert_end?>
                            <uicontrol>Guest List</uicontrol>
                        </menucascade>, choose the guest, click
                                <uicontrol>Book</uicontrol>.<p><image
                                href="../Images/admin/hotel_book_room.png" id="image_hpq_qzt_c2b"
                                width="650"/></p></li>
                    <li>Select <?oxy_insert_start author="Becky" timestamp="20191127T131956+0800"?>a
                        room
                        type<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="Becky" timestamp="20191127T131953+0800" content="the desired room"?>,
                        set the check-in time and check-out time.</li>
                    <li>Click <uicontrol>Save</uicontrol>.</li>
                    <li>Go to <menucascade>
                            <uicontrol>Hotel</uicontrol>
                            <uicontrol>Room Operations</uicontrol>
                            <uicontrol>Booking List</uicontrol>
                        </menucascade>, check if the room is booked with the guest.<p><image
                                href="../Images/admin/hotel_book_status.png" width="650"
                                id="image_jhl_115_c2b"/></p></li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </section>
    </conbody>
</concept>
